.TH ISOT 4 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ Devices"
.SH NAME
.B ISOT
\- ISO Transport over TCP (ISOT)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ISOT
is an implementation of ISO Transport over TCP (ISOT) as described in RFCs.
.[
rfc983
.]
.[
rfc1006
.]
The RFC describes the use of IS 8073
.[
ISO/IEC 8073
.]
ISO Transport Class 0 over TCP/IP (ISOT) by using TCP/IP as a Connection-oriented Network Service
Provider instead of X.25 CONS.
.[
ISO/IEC 8878
.]
.PP
The RFC describes adaptation of TCP to a CONS network service provider through
the use of a 4 byte header used to delimit NPDUs inside of the TCP stream.
.[
$LIST$
.]
